  "text": "As a source of both experimental and predicted interactions, SalmoNet contains information on the transcriptional regulatory targets of various transcription factors based on genome-wide motif scans. In addition, predicted targets of recently characterized transcription factors, such as RtsB, [CITATION_1] which regulates the expression of invasion and flagellar genes, are also provided for future experimental verification and validation. Similar experimental testing and verification can also be performed on the predicted PPIs as well given the importance of PPIs in the survival of Salmonella inside the host cells.",
